    "body": "@paulcbetts try changing in `script/bootstrap.py` should fix the problem.\n\n```\ndef update_node_modules(dirname):\n  with scoped_cwd(dirname):\n    if is_verbose_mode():\n      execute_stdout([NPM, '--target=0.10.36', 'install', '--verbose'])\n    else:\n      execute_stdout([NPM, '--target=0.10.36', 'install'])\n```\n\non a side note, why not let apm take in the node version to download as option if the system already has one [here](https://github.com/atom/apm/blob/master/script/download-node.js#L107) ?\n"
